    <p> My family and I have been to Lupe hundreds, if not thousands of times by now. I could probably buy a car with all the money we've spent there. We're at the point where most of the waiters remember my order. And whenever I'm back in town, I always make sure to stop by Lupe at least once. While you can get good Tex-Mex pretty much anywhere in Houston, I've lived in that city long enough to confidently say this: Lupe is King.</p>
    <h1>Accept No Substitute</h1>
    <p>Like any decent Mexican restaurant, every meal at Lupe starts with complementary chips and salsa. Bean dip is also included - guacamole's available but has to be ordered separately. Probably because we don't shit out avocados like California can. The chips are your standard fare; the salsa and dip are both flavorful in their own right, with the beans being more savory than their spicy counterpart. Open up the menu, however, and you get right to the good stuff.
